subSections.text:
Either from 
* {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*bawk||white}}; cognate with {{cog|mwq|bok}}, {{cog|dao|ɓɔ́ːk}}, {{cog|grt|bok-a}}, {{cog|lif|tr=phɔ}} (STEDT) (confer {{cog|mkh-pro|*kɓɔɔk||white, grey}}).
*: still, Schuessler found *''bawk'''s and its descendants' lack of medial ''-r-'' difficult to reconcile with Sinitic
* or from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*bʷar ~ *pʷar||burn, fire}} with ''-k'' extension, from immediate *'''bar-k''' ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}); cognate with {{och-l|[[皤]]}} "white", {{cog|lus|váar||white, bright}}, Proto-Karenic *'''ʔ(b)wa''' "white".

However, STEDT assigns:
* {{m|lus|váar}} to sub-root {{m|sit-pro|*hwa(ː)r ⪤ *yar}}
* *'''ʔ(b)wa''' to {{m|sit-pro|*b/s-wa}}
* {{och-l|[[燔]]}} to {{m|sit-pro|*bʷar ~ *pʷar}}
* {{och-l|[[皤]]}} to "pan-allofamic" root {{m|sit-pro|*(p/b/h)(w/y)a(ː)(r/l/n/t)}}, all three above being its variants.

